This is a critical security area - many major breaches occur because developers forget to verify that the requesting user is authorized to access the requested data.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
<?php
// api/get_account.php - VULNERABLE: No authorization check
require_once 'config.php';

header('Content-Type: application/json');

$accountId = $_GET['account_id'] ?? null;

if (!$accountId) {
    http_response_code(400);
    echo json_encode(['error' => 'Account ID required']);
    exit;
}

try {
    $pdo = new PDO($dsn, $dbUser, $dbPass);
    $pdo->setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE, PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION);

    // VULNERABLE: Returns ANY account data without checking ownership
    $stmt = $pdo->prepare("SELECT id, name, email, ssn, address, phone, balance FROM accounts WHERE id = ?");
    $stmt->execute([$accountId]);
    $account = $stmt->fetch(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);

    if ($account) {
        echo json_encode($account);
    } else {
        http_response_code(404);
        echo json_encode(['error' => 'Account not found']);
    }
} catch (PDOException $e) {
    http_response_code(500);
    echo json_encode(['error' => 'Database error']);
